channel.title: Typing Tests
channel.description:
So i was wondering what my WPM was then stumbled over this.
http://play.typeracer.com/
i created an account and have played about 40 tests (you play against 5 other players online)
My average WPM is 99, maximum was 122wpm (which is ranked 7 on that quote)
Whats yours?

item.title: Typing Tests
item.dc:creator: @davidude36 Brolapse
item.description:
@davidude36 wrote:

R.I.P RSC:

I had a typing course, but I can’t remember if I had 100 WPM or keystrokes per minute. Well, actually I do: 100 keystrokes a minute equals about 10-30 WPM, so obviously it has to be 100 WPM. It’s been a few years, but I’m shocked by the downturn to 65 WPM. The course was quite expensive too.

Typeracer says that it bases its WPM on 5 key strokes per word. So at 119WPM I’d be doing 595 characters per minute.

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

I’m getting average of 55ishwpm at an average of 97% accuracy, it catches me on a lot words where I don’t read them properly, for example, I wrote grass, instead of glasses, often might miss an of or a. I could probably get 70+wpm if what I’m writing doesn’t have a lot of grammar, but a lot of these examples have hyphens and semi-colons, which I don’t really use that much.
